The &quot;Technical Group&quot; at the Ursuline Convent  were a noisy lot, having their portraits taken on the lawn outside . The photographer welcomed them and said, &quot;Please stand still ladies.&quot;
One lady who was a little deaf, asked her friend, &quot;What did he say?&quot;
&quot;He would like us to stand still.&quot; replied the friend.
Then the photographer asked, &quot;Can you please stand closer so I can focus the camera?&quot;
&quot;What did he say?&quot; asked the first.
&quot;He's going to focus.&quot; replied her friend.
&quot;What, all of us?&quot;

Hence the giggles!  The joke must be at least as old as this photo.
